\begin_layout Section*
Data and Descriptive Statistics
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We will be using the Uganda National Household Survey (UNHS) 2005/06.
 While being somewhat dated, we have chosen this survey because it has much
 more information on agriculture than the more recent UNHS of 2009/10.
 Structured with a standard Living Standard Measurement Survey - Integrated
 Survey on Agriculture (LSMS-ISA) in mind, the UNHS 2005/06 collected detailed
 information on a sample of almost 43000 people in 7500 households in Uganda.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The selection of children is base on the household roster.
 In particluar, we will select individuals that respond they are son or
 daughter of the household head.
 In Uganda, as in most developing countries, households are often extended,
 encompassing several generations.
 This means that such a strategy may also select adults that are son or
 daughter, but never moved out.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From this sample, we select households that are headed by couples that are
